title: For Sale/Trade:  Vintage .38 SPL
postcontent: Very neat and well maintained vintage .38 SW revolver. Six round cylinder, interesting history, was originally a SW revolver supposedly sent through the Lend Lease Act to English forces where it was chambered in an English round. Tons of info on the revolver itself, unfortunately I do not know too much about it. Barrel is marked .38" .767" and the revolver has many stampings of BNP (British National Party). Cyclinder is marked England and serialized to match the frame. Frame is marked made in USA and has the SW square butt k frame look with the serial numbers on the bottom of the grip. The chamber shows evidence of being rechambered from .38 SW to .38 Spl showing the second ledge inside the chamber. This is a firearm that really belongs with someone who knows a good deal about revovlers or is willing to do some research!
